{{distinguish|Krio language}} {{Infobox language |name=Bahasa Dayak Krio |nativename=Kereho |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=[[West Kalimantan]] |speakers=500 |date=2003 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Kayan–Murik languages|Kayan–Murik]] |fam4=Muller-Schwaner 'Punan' |dia1=Seputan |iso3=xke |glotto=kere1285 |glottorefname=Kereho }}
'''Krio Dayak''' is a [[Kayan languages|Kayan language]] of the [[Krio Dayak people]] in [[West Kalimantan]], [[Indonesia]].
Examples of Krio Dayak language:- {| class="wikitable" |- ! Krio Dayak language ! [[Banjar language]] ! Meaning |- | cucul | salukut | burn |- | julak | julak | eldest uncle or aunt |- | nongah | angah | middle uncle or aunt |- | busu' | busu | youngest uncle or aunt |- | osa | asa | one |- | dua | dua | two |- | tiga | talu / tiga | three |- | ompat | ampat | four |- | limak | lima | five |- | anam | anam | six |- | tujuh | tujuh / pitu | seven |- | lapatn | lapan / walu | eight |- | semilatn | sambilan | nine |- | sapuluh | sapuluh | ten |}
